dc_title_s: Central America, Panama--Costa Rica, Río Colorado to Cristóbal (Raster Image)
dc_description_s: Prepared and published by the Defense Mapping Agency. Depths shown by isolines and soundings. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. "From various sources to 1983." "Copyright 1996 by the United States Government. No copyright claimed under Title 17 U.S.C." "Soundings in meters." Insets: Isla Escudo de Veraguas. Scale 1:75,000 -- Continuation of Río Colorado to Cristóbal. Includes compilation diagram and index to next larger scale charts. Map No. 26070. This map is part of a collection of scanned and georeferenced nautical charts produced by the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA). United States. Defense Mapping Agency. (1996). Central America, Panama--Costa Rica, Río Colorado to Cristóbal (Raster Image). LandInfo. Available at: https://purl.stanford.edu/fc347xn7595 This layer is presented in the WGS84 coordinate system for web display purposes. Downloadable data are provided in native coordinate system or projection.
